SIMPLE: instrument
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Instrument
<hw>In"stru*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>instrument</ets>, L. <ets>instrumentum</ets>. See
<er>Instruct</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>That by means of which any work is performed, or
result is effected; a tool; a utensil; an implement; a device; <as>as,
the <ex>instruments</ex> of a mechanic; astronomical
<ex>instruments</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the lofty <qex>instruments</qex> of war.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A contrivance or implement, by which musical sounds
are produced; <as>as, a musical <ex>instrument</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Praise him with stringed <qex>instruments</qex> and organs.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. cl. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But signs when songs and <qex>instruments</qex> he hears.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A writing, as the means of giving
formal expression to some act; a writing expressive of some act,
contract, process, as a deed, contract, writ, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, is made a means, or is
caused to serve a purpose; a medium, means, or agent; <as>as, their army
was primarily an <ex>instrument</ex> of oppression</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or useful serving man and <qex>instrument</qex>,⟦br⟧
To any sovereign state.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The bold are but the <qex>instruments</qex> of the wise.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Tool; implement; utensil; machine; apparatus;
channel; agent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instrument</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Instrument
<hw>In"stru*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
perform upon an instrument; to prepare for an instrument; <as>as, a
sonata <ex>instrumented</ex> for orchestra</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To furnish or equip with instruments; to attach
instruments to; <as>as, the fighter planes were heavily
<ex>instrumented</ex>; the patient was <ex>instrumented</ex> to monitor
him remotely</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instrumental</ent>⟦br⟧
